item.dc:creator: @4you111 4you111
item.description:
@4you111 wrote:

lildude783:

theres no point in using the .class files … it is very hard to decompile it. the way u change it is u go into the EGUI.java file (the notepad) and write ur server’s name in the quotations ("") and then save it. Then it will change the .class file when u compile it using the BATCH file. Then when its done compiling it … load up ur client and the preset IP adress will be “urservername.no-ip.biz” ok? do u get it now!

yea i tryed adn compiled nothnig worked maybe i did something wrong?
